  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Vietnam River Network</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Overall aim: to promote the community and expert#s participations in water and river governance in Vietnam.
The ultimate aim of this project is to create more opportunities for communities and NGOs to participate in water governance in Vietnam through specific advocacy works.  To achieve so, the public advocacy approach puts stress in building capacity for communities in the first place so that they can contribute their ideas more effectively in local issues. Meanwhile, policy advocacy approach finds opportunities for experts and advocates to express their ideas in revision process of a specific law - the Law on Irrigation, which is implemented in 2016. At the same time, Vietnam Rivers Network will review its Advocacy Strategy 2014-2020 and keep it up to date, along with producinga detailed Action Plan. Communication will assist amplifying all the above-mentioned Objectives through a redesigned website. The details of each Objective is expressed below will review its Advocacy Strategy 2014-2020 and keep it up to date, along with producinga detailed Action Plan. Communication will assist amplifying all the above-mentioned Objectives through a redesigned website.
The specific objectives are:
- Objective 1: To improve community participation in water governance in the Mekong Delta through PIM approach and Story of Change
- Objective 2: To contribute to a more inclusive Law on Irrigation revision process
- Objective 3: To review and update Vietnam Rivers Network#s Advocacy Strategy and develop its Action Plan
- Objective 4: To make Vietnam Rivers Network#s website a platform to share VRN#s advocacy works and incorporate maps of at least 3 river basins in Vietnam onto the website.</narrative>
  </description>
  <participating-org role="4" type="90">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Center for Water Resources Conserva</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WARECOD is a local Vietnamese NGO focusing on water resources management and conservation in 8 provinces in Northern Highland, Central Higland, and in Mekong delta. Warecod has 3 core programs:
1. research
2. Community development
3. Vietnam River Network (VRN)

WARECOD currently has 15 staff and 4 volunteers. For any area they start with research to go to community development.
WARECOD has highly professional staff but may need some improvements/attention for organizational structure and functioning.

WARECOD has a lot of interest in a partnership with Oxfam given the important relationship in disaster preparedness and water management work and likesto start/ improve their ability for response in the areas they work.

WARECOD can contribute with
# Water management/governance/CCA, for communities development and preparedness through capacity building
# community based and policy influence based on that work (mainly at districts level)
# river basin management
# work with vulnerable ethnic minority communities</narrative>
